Long ago, there were four great nations in this world.

The Fire Nation, the Water Nation, the Wind Nation, and the
Thunder Nation. They have official names, but... that's not
important right now.

The people of Fire were bright and passionate, valuing their
comrades above all else. The people of Water prized fairness
as a virtue and possessed a righteousness that adhered to
discipline.

The people of Wind were compassionate and gentle, loving
nature and living in harmony with it. The people of Thunder
were wise and quick-witted, using their intelligence to
create machinery.
What triggered it and who started it is not important.

Humans are not made to accept "what is different." As such,
conflict was inevitable.

For their own sake, they excluded others, imposed their
justice, mercy led to tragedy, and machinery became a tool
for killing.

This went on for generations, as people continued to
decrease in number, all while sincerely praying for "their
own" peace.

In this world, there are Demon Lords, monsters, and heroes
fighting to protect the peace. It may very well be the most
significant thing of all.

But for the majority, such matters are of no concern... Even
in "such a world," most people live their petty lives, each
burdened with their own worries.

Some run shops, others till the fields. There are those who
fight to protect the town from monsters, and those who just
laze about in safety.

Everyone has their own "way of life," doing their best with
what they can, or maybe just slacking off for just today.

I may not be involved in the "fate of the world," but I want
to leave behind many marks of my sharpened claws.
